<subSubSection id="B9AD2C5A49851583821248D48BFAA797" pageId="null" pageNumber="565" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="6CC925D809C5495EEF1EDF4C62BA8C0C" pageId="null" pageNumber="565">Insubrischer Lauch</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="A9A8F3AB1F13F4F988F16A83471AB1FC" pageId="null" pageNumber="565" type="description">
<paragraph id="066A3662DBA527D6FF7E4D1B4BDEA50A" pageId="null" pageNumber="565">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="7430EF22C83DE1808B7DA42BB27EBDF2" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="null" pageNumber="565" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="narcissiflorum">
<emphasis id="14AD2AE09316B1637109F9A2B07F474E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="565">A. narcissiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 9) durch folgende Merkmale: 
<emphasis id="248C98EA37E20AB9F52E9B7F833CC9A5" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="565">
Zwiebel von 
<normalizedToken id="6A9EEF666BE494FD0AE7C2A852B69C51" originalValue="Häuten" pageId="null" pageNumber="565">Haeuten</normalizedToken>
umgeben, diese nicht in Fasern zerfallend; 
<normalizedToken id="EEFCF2A3FE549D94435A8A681D503907" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="565">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
und Fruchtstand nickend
</emphasis>
(bei den andern Arten unserer Flora aufrecht). - 
<normalizedToken id="388BEE66EA8FF3A37C6617BF8781F824" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="565">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F27672904EC4E33D5FB8361EF3DBCC01" pageId="null" pageNumber="565">
<emphasis id="A6AA2EB75722B96604031D48B90E49E8" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="565">Zytologische Angaben. 2n = 14:</emphasis>
Material von der Grigna (Comerseegebiet); Chromosomen sehr 
<normalizedToken id="2D5CDAAC72BC368FE91E0A53A4A8CF76" originalValue="ähnlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="565">aehnlich</normalizedToken>
denen von 
<taxonomicName id="8D2133F2D49A99841715D41A3ACADB89" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="null" pageNumber="565" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="narcissiflorum">
<emphasis id="4A263AA258B779065F6FA9914C0DC1FA" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="565">A. narcissiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 9) (Favarger 1959).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E8C024561E276769F3EB6CD8C4CB9C1" pageId="null" pageNumber="565">
<emphasis id="28FE9DA52ABFF04167BB83B3CE1DE556" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="565">Standort.</emphasis>
Subalpin. Wie 
<taxonomicName id="19F4E69651603F14A27F7DA368135D59" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="null" pageNumber="565" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="narcissiflorum">
<emphasis id="4B5325311A2DB4F39D974387123075D4" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="565">A. narcissiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 9).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="193DE41B041E89B06B0EFA223B136EB5" pageId="null" pageNumber="565">
<emphasis id="865D91B0CD751C72A6A724916DBE8041" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="565">Verbreitung. Bergamasker Pflanze:</emphasis>
Bergamasker Alpen vom Comersee (Grigna) bis Brescia (Corna Blacca).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
